<br>
I predict this is going to crash pretty hard-core in the U.S.<br>
<br>
People really only have one of two reasons to buy this: because it's FF, or because it's MMORPG.<br>
<br>
Most of the existing FF fans in the U.S. probably don't want to see FF turned into a MMORPG. At least not as a proper sequel. If they had taken this out of sequence and released it as a spin-off like FF Tactics, Square might have pulled it off. But I think the FF purists will lynch mob it because it isn't FF. So there goes the first reason for a big chunk of the market.<br>
<br>
Square's only hope is that MMORPGers (who couldn't care less if it's FF or not) will buy it. Two big problems. First, the MMORPG market is getting awfully crowded here. Most of the MMORPGs on the market come from established MMORPG franchises. As a newcomer, they're going to have to fight tooth and nail if they want any market share at all. Second, you need a PS2 with a network adapter to even play FFXI, and how many people do you know who have that? Plus, MMORPGers expect to be able to talk to one another, and I don't see that happening without a keyboard add-on as well. That adds up to a lot of money -- money that could be paying the next two or three months of another MMORPG.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I like the series, but I'm really questioning Square's business sense lately. First the technically amazing, but unprecidentedly *bad* movie, and now a totally radical departure from the formula that made their franchise what it is today. I'm beginning to think that they're trying to run FF into the ground... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3179<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/03 3:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1733.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Final Fantasy XI (FF MMORPG)</span><hr size=1> FFXI will also available as a PC game, not just Playstation 2.  You can play it on either system and all the characters are in the same game world (regardless of whether you're playing on a PS2 or playing from a PC).<br>
<br>
From the little bit about the game I've been able to find (in English), it sounds like they're trying to make it story driven, which is why they designated it as FFXI rather than a spinoff (like FF Tactics).  Additional expansions will expand the storyline further (the US release will actually be the game + the first expansion).  <br>
<br>
Gameplaywise, a lot of the stuff sounds fun.  Everyone gets their own house (complete w/ a Moogle) and you can decorate it however you like, and you can grow plants and ride chocobos and airships and such.  I checked out some screenshots and they look pretty cool.  It certainly looks like a FF game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
